{"arkId":"cl010102525","url":"https:\/\/collections.louvre.fr\/ark:\/53355\/cl010102525","modified ":"2025-10-04","title":"Vase cylindrique \u00e0 couvercle, d\u0027une paire (avec TH 450)","titleComplement":"","denominationTitle":[{"type":"Titre","value":"Vase cylindrique \u00e0 couvercle, d\u0027une paire (avec TH 450)"}],"displayDateCreated":"Epoque \/ p\u00e9riode : \u00e9poque Kangxi =  Kang Hsi = Kang-Hsi (1662-1722) (Chine-\u003Edynastie Qing (1644-1911))\r\n\r\nDate de cr\u00e9ation\/fabrication : vers 1710","currentLocation":"Richelieu, [OArt] Salle 550 - Elise Dosne-Thiers, Vitrine 5, Etag\u00e8re 3","room":"Salle 550, Aile Aile Richelieu, Niveau 1","isMuseesNationauxRecuperation":false,"dateCreated":[{"startYear":1710,"endYear":"","imprecision":"vers","text":"D\u00e9but du XVIIIe si\u00e8cle","type":"Date de cr\u00e9ation\/fabrication","doubt":""}],"creator":[{"label":"Chine, atelier de Jingdezhen","attributionLevel":"Attribution actuelle","linkType":"","creatorRole":"","authenticationType":"","doubt":"","attributedBy":"","attributedYear":"","wikidata":""}],"objectNumber":[{"value":"TH 449","type":"Num\u00e9ro principal"}],"collection":"D\u00e9partement des Objets d\u0027art du Moyen Age, de la Renaissance et des temps modernes","printsDrawingsEntity":"","printsDrawingsCollection":"","objectType":"vase, r\u00e9cipient","originalObject":"","printState":"","description":"Vase du type \u0022famille verte\u0022: une femme, debout sous un palmier, tient un vase de fleurs en forme de bouteille au goulot \u00e9vas\u00e9, et vient l\u0027offrir \u00e0 une femme assise qui, plac\u00e9e sous un bambou, tient un \u00e9ventail. Des cl\u00f4tures vertes ceignent un jardin sous-entendu.\r\nDes palmettes r\u00e9guli\u00e8res entourent le col du vase et surmontent une mosa\u00efque pav\u00e9e \u00e0 r\u00e9serve de pivoines.\r\nLa caract\u00e9ristique du d\u00e9cor est qu\u0027il s\u0027agit d\u0027\u00e9maux translucides pos\u00e9s sur la couverte, ce qui donne une grande luminosit\u00e9 et une belle brillance. Il est compl\u00e9t\u00e9 par quelques touches dor\u00e9es sur des d\u00e9tails choisis.\r\n\r\nLes pieds et les couvercles sont en cuivre dor\u00e9.","inscriptions":"Inscription : \r ; I et une croix sous le pied","namesAndTitles":"","onomastics":"","dimension":[{"type":"Hauteur","value":"28,2","displayDimension":"28,2 cm","unit":"cm","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":1,"note":""},{"type":"Diam\u00e8tre","value":"9,7","displayDimension":"9,7 cm","unit":"cm","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":2,"note":""}],"shape":"","materialsAndTechniques":"Mat\u00e9riau : porcelaine\r\nTechnique : techniques c\u00e9ramique\r\nMat\u00e9riau : cuivre (dor\u00e9)","placeOfCreation":"Chine (Asie-\u003EAsie orientale = Extr\u00eame Orient)","dateOfDiscovery":"","placeOfDiscovery":"","provenance":"","historicalContext":[],"objectHistory":"Collection Adolphe Thiers (Les potiches TH 449 et TH 450 se trouvaient dans la chambre de Thiers qui les avait choisies parmi les plus pr\u00e9cieuses de sa collection (cf. Ch. Blanc)); legs Elise Dosne Thiers, 1880, suivant les volont\u00e9s de son mari Adolphe Thiers et sous r\u00e9serve d\u2019usufruit de sa s\u0153ur F\u00e9licie Dosne qui y renonce et ex\u00e9cute le legs en 1881.","jabachInventory":"","napoleonInventory":"","previousOwner":[{"value":"Mme Dosne-Thiers, Elise","note":"","role":", Donateur"},{"value":"M. Thiers, Louis Adolphe","note":"","role":", Collectionneur"}],"acquisitionDetails":[{"mode":"legs sous r\u00e9serve d\u0027usufruit","doubt":"","dates":[{"type":"date d\u0027arriv\u00e9e au Mus\u00e9e","value":"1881","startYear":1881,"endYear":1881}]}],"ownedBy":"Etat","heldBy":"Mus\u00e9e du Louvre, D\u00e9partement des Objets d\u0027art du Moyen Age, de la Renaissance et des temps modernes","longTermLoanTo":"","index":{"Mode d\u0027acquisition":[{"value":"legs sous r\u00e9serve d\u0027usufruit"}],"period":[{"value":"\u00e9poque Kangxi =  Kang Hsi = Kan